One of the leading Peoples Democratic Party Presidential aspirants Senator Anyim Pius Anyim has demanded the zoning of his Party’s Presidential ticket to the South if they want PDP to win the 2023 Presidential election. Anyim gave this charge on Monday in Jos while on a Campaign visit to the Plateau chapter of the PDP to woo them to support his candidature for the Presidential ticket of the Party in the forthcoming Presidential primary of the party. He told Plateau Party Faithfuls and its leadership that both North and South have capable and qualified Presidential materials that can provide quality leadership for this country. He hinted that as former Senate President and Secretary to the federal government of Nigeria, he is imminently qualified to fly his party Presidential ticket in 2023. .The former Senate President added that the founding fathers of PDP thought it wise to enshrine in the party’s constitution zoning to give all sections of the country a sense of belonging to Nigeria Nation. According to him, it is not true that only Presidential Aspirants with Northern backgrounds can win elections, saying Presidential Aspirants from the Southern party will win elections if qualified to stand elections. Anyim further stressed that 2023 would be a defining moment for his party and Nigerians to do the right thing for the sake of togetherness. He promised to make Jos the centre of Tourism and unity of this country if he wins the 2023 Presidential election. POLL He also challenged the People of Plateau to vote for PDP in all the elections in 2023, saying Plateau is the home of the Peoples’ Democratic party in Nigeria.